       <div id="dv_story_dtls">
        <p>
         Two bodies were found as rescuers searched Wednesday for five French nationals missing after their boat capsized off Malta.
         <br/>
         <br/>
         The bodies found late Tuesday were expected to be identified as Marie Grimaud, 38, and Sandrine Gaudet, 36, the Times of Malta newspaper reported.
         <br/>
         <br/>
         The women were last seen Sunday with Philippe Grimaud, 41; Elias Chnouni, 49; and his son Eli, 14, as they left on a 3.5-metre boat from a bay on the island of Gozo. The boat was later found capsized with a life jacket floating nearby.
         <br/>
         <br/>
         The 18-metre cabin cruiser they were holidaying on was anchored in another bay. Fishermen reported that winds suddenly picked up Sunday night.
         <br/>
         <br/>
         "In a small boat without proper rowing experience, you'd be in trouble," one fisherman told the Times.
         <br/>
         <br/>
         Maltese, Italian and American aircraft were involved in the search.
         <br/>
         <br/>
         -Sapa-dpa
        </p>
